e transformed the meaning of fatherhood among the urban poor. Intimate interviews with more than 100 fathers make real the significant obstacles faced by low-income men at every step in the familial process: from the difficulties of romantic relationships, to decision-making dilemmas at conception, to the often celebratory moment of birth, and finally to the hardships that accompany the early years of the child's life, and beyond.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aFatherhoodzUnited States. 0aPoor childrenzUnited States. 0aSingle fatherszUnited States. 0aUnmarried fatherszUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aanthropology.  ablended families.  acareer.  acharacter.  achildren.  aclass.  acultural changes.  adeadbeat dads.  aengaging.  afamilial process.  afamily.  afatherhood.  agender and sex.  agender studies.  ahuman rights.  aincarceration.  ainner city men.  amorals.  apoverty.  aprison.  arace and culture.  arace.  arelationships.  aromantic relationships.  asocial issues.  asocial problems.  asocial science.  asocial work.  asocioeconomic studies.  asociology of urban areas.  asociology.  aunderstanding men and boys.  aunmarried fathers.  aunwed fatherhood.  aurban issues.  aurban poor.  avirtue.1 aNelson, Timothy J., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052027406840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095513440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520955134423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520955134/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP 